Officials ordered the evacuation of coastal areas within a 5-kilometer radius of the volcano, with over 11,000 people fleeing their homes. Authorities continue to monitor the situation and urge residents to stay informed and follow evacuation instructions.

name: Smoking ban UK
summary: The UK House of Commons has passed a bill that will prohibit anyone born after 2009 from purchasing cigarettes. This measure aims to create a "smoke-free" generation by phasing out tobacco use among younger people. The bill has sparked controversy, with some Conservative MPs opposing it. Critics argue that the ban infringes on personal freedom and will be difficult to enforce. However, supporters maintain that it is necessary to protect public health and reduce the number of smoking-related deaths. The bill still needs to pass through the House of Lords before becoming law. If implemented, it would be the most stringent tobacco control measure in the world.
